The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, April 21, 2004 				 Audiovisual bonanza
																								Dhrubajit Bhattacharya is the voice that HMV chose to promote at the Artists Circle earlier this month. It was an occasion graced by artists from various fields wherein P.C. Sorcar represented the world of magic that he has come to become synonymous with. V. Balsara inaugurated Dhrubajits Jagat Janani, a collection of songs that has inspired the exhibition that is currently on at Artists Circle. The Deities is an exhibition that features the works of Suhas Roy, Shuvaprasanna, Prakash Karmakar, Biswajit Mondal among others; Subrata Gangopadhyays oil on canvas features alongside. The Deities exudes uniqueness in its very conception: it is an exhibition that is born out of the strains of the universal language of music.																								Event: An exhibition of paintings based on the audio album Jagat Janani																								When: Till April 26; 11 am - 7 pm																								Where: Artists Circle, 46 Circus Avenue
